# Repository hygiene

## CI artifacts (never commit)

Do not add or commit:

- `coverage.xml`, `.coverage`, `htmlcov/`
- `tests/smoke/artifacts/*` (except this README)
- Runtime outputs under `data/`, `output/`, `tests/golden/artifacts/`

Smoke and benchmark binaries (`.pptx`, `.pdf`, screenshots) belong in GitHub Actions
artifacts unless they are an explicitly reviewed golden baseline under
`tests/golden/` or `tests/benchmark/`.

## Documentation discipline

Per task, prefer **at most one** of each:

- Update an existing formal design/architecture doc
- Update `CHANGELOG.md`
- Update a single implementation status file (e.g. `docs/QUALITY_GATE_STATUS.md`)

Do **not** create new `COMPLETE_*`, `FINAL_*`, `SESSION_SUMMARY_*`, or duplicate
`*_SUMMARY.md` files for every feature. Session notes belong under
`.dev-notes/docs-history/`, not `docs/`.

## Deployment scope

Docker, install packages, and cross-platform deployment work are **deferred** until
product quality gates are met (human visual review, real-project acceptance, visual E2E).
Do not expand deployment docs or scripts unless explicitly requested.
